a.xlink:title: Distribution of earnings to shareholders, paid for in cash, stock, scrip issue or, rarely, in kind, for example, in company products or property. The dividend amount is decided by the board of directors.
Specifies the value expressed as a rate or an amount. For example, the value of a tax or a commission.
Financial instruments representing a sum of rights of the investor vis-a-vis the issuer.

Definition of the cash proceeds for a corporate action in generic terms; that is, before applying it to specific securities holding. An example would be the definition of a dividend payment where all the information will be given in general on a per share basis.
Obligation for the debtor to pay the creditor an amount of cash.
Amount of money due to the government or tax authority, according to various pre-defined parameters such as thresholds or income.
Distributions in cash and/or securities following a corporate event.
